@startuml component-password-bridge
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because the security-critical point is WHERE the secret travels — main-side only,
'' revealed straight into the web-view, never through the renderer UI — which the concept colours make
'' explicit (slate = main.passwords, amber = the bridge/seam, red = the secret path). Mermaid's ad-hoc
'' classDef cannot bind a colour to a suite-wide concept.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Password-manager bridge — the secret is revealed main-side, straight into the web-view

component "web page form\n(login inputs)" as Page RENDERER_TINT
component "web-preload.js\n(isolated bridge in the web-view)" as WP IPC_TINT
component "vinary.main.passwords\n(provider adapters)" as Main MAIN_TINT
component "provider CLI\n(1Password / LastPass / ...)\nspawned argv, no shell" as CLI FS_TINT
component "Renderer UI\n(picker / save prompt)" as R RENDERER_TINT

Page --> WP : form metadata /\nsave candidate
WP --> Main : form metadata /\nsave candidate
R --> Main : selected item id /\nsave token (NON-secret)
Main --> CLI : spawn argv array (no shell)
CLI --> Main : provider response
Main --> R : sanitized metadata\n(NO secret)
Main --> WP : **revealed secret ONLY**
WP --> Page : DOM input / change events

note right of Main #F5E1E0: the secret never enters the\nRenderer UI, app-db, or config —\nit goes main -> web-preload -> the form

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| web page / renderer UI |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| web-preload bridge (seam) |
  |<#3A5BA0>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| main.passwords / provider CLI |
  Non-secret metadata may reach the UI; the revealed secret goes only main -> web-preload -> form.
endlegend
@enduml
